.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-me - Manage your own account (export data, request deletion, cancel)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock me [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
User-self surface for GDPR Art. 15 / 17 and APP 12 / 13.

.PP
bcdock me show              → identity + status + deletion schedule (if any)
  bcdock me export            → request a ZIP of all data we hold for you
  bcdock me delete            → schedule account deletion in 30 days
  bcdock me cancel-deletion   → reverse a pending deletion

.PP
Auth: requires a JWT or API key bound to your account.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for me


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock me show
  bcdock me export --wait
  bcdock me delete --confirm you@example.com
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock(1)\fP, \fBbcdock-me-billing(1)\fP, \fBbcdock-me-cancel-deletion(1)\fP, \fBbcdock-me-delete(1)\fP, \fBbcdock-me-export(1)\fP, \fBbcdock-me-show(1)\fP
